reviews.text: My co-workers and I went for lunch Saturday to catch up, enjoy awesome food and cozy beverages,  this place did not disappoint! From there, absolutely excellent food to the charismatic atmosphere, we had an excellent experience.  The service was top notch, the owner goes above and beyond and the several different appetizers were mouth-watering! Everything was cooked and seasoned to perfection.  The trendy and fun atmosphere makes me definitely want to come back for another experience, as well as try more options on their menu. The establishment was very clean and very welcoming.  Good Job guys!! If you are in the area , you should check them out!!

Great food and service, and awesome Tuesday night trivia! House cocktails are all incredible, a little light and sweet, but well-balanced and delicious - the frozen espresso martini, azalea lemonade, and mint julep are all fantastic must tries if you're into those drinks or cocktails in general. Dog Park app is a great sampler, everything rocks, especially the stromboli! House salad is very nice, and can't go wrong with Quattro Formaggio Pizza special or Cookies and Cream Dessert Pizza.

Absolutely delicious! The pizzas were so good and cheesy and fluffy. The chicken tenders were huge and very good with the honey mustard-type sauce. Reasonably priced, as well. Only suggestion is please add a kids option for chicken tenders in a smaller portion at a kids meal price. We will definitely be back!
Great food and service but the beer isn‚Äôt great.  Average at best and pretty pricy.  Pretzel was good but $15!

Not a beer drinker? Not a problem because Wasserhund is serving up some GOOD food!!! The specialty soup today was TUSCAN BEAN & SAUSAGE... OMG just get a bowl!! ü§© it's good!

The Beer Bratwurst with their made from scratch beer bratwurst; served on a bratwurst bun with sauerkraut and beer mustard was DELICIOUS!

The Small Burly Bulldog with House Red Sauce topped with House Blend Cheese, Pepperoni, Italian Sausage, Bacon and cubed Ham on a soft, buttery crust was amazing dipped in their smooth ranch dressing -- NO PIZZA BONES leftover from this pizza!!! üòãüòÇ

JAMES was very pleasant & made this 1st visit so enjoyable! Can't wait to return!!

HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!

Highly recommend the spicy red sauce on the pizza, gives things a nice kick without being overwhelming.  Beer is always cold, crisp, and delicious.

detailedReviews.text: Im from California and think the beers are the best. But this place is built different. Every single beer form light to IPAs was amazing. I had a few flights and beersto go and they all were so freakin good. I got a pizza and the oreo pizza that were delicious  too. Highly recommend this places.I‚Äôm def coming back when I visit. Oh can‚Äôt forget about the service, they‚Äôre on top of it and always coming around. Just too good üôåüèΩ

detailedReviews.author: Angie H
detailedReviews.text: For being one of the busiest nights, the manager Grayson was going above and beyond for everyone that walked in the door. Anybody would have been overwhelmed in the volume of customers, but she wore the night effortlessly. Thank you, Grayson, for being so kind! Jamie, our waitress, was a doll! So available and sweet. Again even with the crowd, she was giving her time and attention and laughing along with us. Thank you, Jamie, for being so welcoming and a great night! Moral of the story: definitely come here... but come EARLY for music bingo. And as always, tip yo bartenders!

detailedReviews.author: Nicole Burns
detailedReviews.text: So much fun at 90s bingo! Waitress so accommodating with our toddler too

"I didn't really care for them to be honest. When I think brewery, that's not what I think of." -Wife

I liked the beer cheese and orange crush IPA.

detailedReviews.author: Scott R
detailedReviews.text: Amazing food and beer. Great atmosphere and customer service. Not only this location, but Virginia Beach as well. Henry, Eric, Megan, and Alex are always amazing. I would recommend going and checking it out. The Chicken schnitzel sandwich and of course pizza is amazing.

detailedReviews.author: William Bungy
detailedReviews.text: Amazing place.  I will definitely be back!

detailedReviews.author: Nicole Madison
detailedReviews.text: Wasserhund is always a great experience whether dine-in or carry-out. The food is terrific and always made in a timely fashion ( even on Super Bowl Sunday.) We also love the gluten free options and that there is a table and food for our pups too.

detailedReviews.author: Amyra Anderson
detailedReviews.text: Very Happy with our service. Great food!

detailedReviews.author: Samantha M
detailedReviews.text: Love the food and friendly service!!

detailedReviews.author: Benjamin Golub
detailedReviews.text: Food was amazing, atmosphere was perfect, it was such a great night to eat outside! They had a big group come in so the food was a little delayed but worth the wait!

detailedReviews.author: Bay Barber Co
detailedReviews.text: Our favorite pizza in the area. The crust is so good. The other food options are also great, and lots of beer to choose from. Inside is clean and comfortable and they have a nice outdoor seating area.

detailedReviews.author: Randy Gressley
detailedReviews.text: Wife and I had lunch after shopping. Excellent pizza and beer.

detailedReviews.author: henry lee
detailedReviews.text: Eric, our favorite beverage technician, as always, comes through with the best service! Food was perfect, atmosphere was great, and the beverage was cold!

detailedReviews.author: Steve Fanelty

detailedReviews.author: Gary Bowden
detailedReviews.text: Great beer and food!

detailedReviews.author: Terri
detailedReviews.text: We hosted a group of 10 at this location tonight and we were so disappointed in the food. We normally go to the Hilltop location and cannot rave about Hilltop's food enough. Chesapeake location's food was not even close, it was pretty awful...so bad that we will never go there again.  The service was slow but they seemed to be understaffed so no fault of the staff.  Please don't bother with opening a second location if you can't even come close to the original.

detailedReviews.text: Ordered a pizza ( Burly Bulldog ) appetizer ( Puppy Tails ) and a beer ( Tall Bark and Handsome A+ ) All three were great! Eric had perfect service. Food delivered hot and beer was cold. Thank you! For the great meal.

detailedReviews.author: Jill Clark
detailedReviews.text: Great place. Moved to Chesapeake last year and this place by far, is the best spot I've found in my area. Food was great, a Rueben pizza? Who knew I needed this in my life? It was so good. Shout out to the beers on tap too. Good selection - nice and cold. Atmosphere was fun and the staff is great. I  am so glad I found this place. Highly recommend.

detailedReviews.author: Skip Morrow
detailedReviews.text: Love this place! Longing for warmer weather so we can eat/drink outside!

detailedReviews.author: Steven Hamilton
detailedReviews.text: I've been looking forward to trying their pizza. It could've been really good; almost great. However, my pie and every other one I saw come from the serving window had undercooked crust. I'm hoping that this was just one night because the sauce were good.

detailedReviews.text: My co-workers and I went for lunch Saturday to catch up, enjoy awesome food and cozy beverages,  this place did not disappoint! Good Job guys!! If you are in the area , you should check them out!!

detailedReviews.author: paul matticks
detailedReviews.text: One of our favorite brewery stops, weather the Chesapeake lication or the Virginia Beach lication. The pizzas are always great, the chicken tenders with the sweet Thai chili are delicious. A great selection of wonderful beers and always amazing service!! A must stop for good beers a d good foods.

detailedReviews.author: Phillip Railsback
detailedReviews.text: So I finally came here after having their awesome Doggy Paddle IPA at Pups and Pints, and I didn't realize Wasserhund Brewing was so close to me, and I was finally able to make it here. I came in when it wasn't busy at, which is how I prefer it, and it was a great experience. I got the doggy pattle ipa again and it is just as good as I remember, and I had their beer bratwurst for lunch, which I thought was absolutely amazing and delicious. The bartender was very accomodating and friendly, props to him. Its a smaller place, but it also has an outside patio, and the vibe here is very nice. I loved it here. Very good experience for my first time here and I'm glad I was able to make it here finally. Highly recommend it here!

detailedReviews.author: Mackenzie Berry
detailedReviews.text: Amazing mozzarella sticks that were clearly made in house (and not just frozen and reheated as is often the case). Pizza is also fabulous, and they have a vegan/vegetarian meat substitute which is delicious! 10/10, would definitely go back!

detailedReviews.author: Amanda Jackson
detailedReviews.text: I sat here no one came to serve me they kept walking by

detailedReviews.author: John Morehouse
detailedReviews.text: We love Wasserhund!  The food is always amazing and we've recently moved to the "we are going to try everything" phase of things!  We went there last Friday night, it was pretty busy, Kiara was our server and even while new-ish to the place, she rocked it!  We love the food and the atmosphere so definitely worth going if you like good pizza. Plus, sometimes you get to pet a dog and that always makes a person happy.  =)

detailedReviews.author: Steve Schweizer
detailedReviews.text:
I went there for lunch because i was over in the area. I got the dog bones. They were really good, but it did take 4 napkins to soak up the grease. Then I tried the vegan brat. It wasn't terrible, but was very dry, and the bun was a little over toasted. Bartender recommended the tots...spot on, they were probably some of the besr I have ever had, but the portions....so small. I had the stout. It was pretty good.

Service - Awesome. Bartender was really nice and helpful. He checked on me several times.
Food - If the cheesy bread (Dogbones) wasn't so incredibly greasy (there was literally a pool in the center and underneath) I would say it was great, but that really detracted. Sorry I didn't get a pic. The Brat $14 for a small brat and no side??? Casualt pint has the drunken brat with Fries for $11. That was dry and really over priced. Tots were the saving grace today.

If you are coming for pizza and beer, you should do ok. But, i definitely would not recommend any sandwiches or brats that don't come with a side. Just way to overpriced. Apps....roll the dice.  once I sopped up the grease, they were good. I had a pretzel at the other location, it was good....guessing it's the same food here. I had 2 beers the dog bones and a brat with tots and it was $50. $50 for lunch. That was before the tip.

detailedReviews.author: Todd Brooks
detailedReviews.text: So I made a huge Uber order mistake and Wasserhund took care of everything with no charges. This is my favorite beer and pizza establishment in the entire region and the customer service is impeccable. Alex canceled my order in record time and made sure I wouldn‚Äôt be charged for my mistake. Love IT

detailedReviews.author: Macius Darkwood
detailedReviews.text: Came in with my family for lunch. We had an assortment of appetizers while waiting on the last of our group. For entrees I split the Bulldog pizza with my niece(no survivors). We had the Bratwurst, Schnitzel sandwich, etc. The Brussel Sprout were amazing. Pizza crust flavorful. Overall, we had some great food and enjoyed the company of our server, Caleb. Thank you üôèüëç great job! üíØ

detailedReviews.author: Christina Gaffos
detailedReviews.text: Great food. Great beer. The waitress was very helpful and attentive. Even a waitress that was not ours stopped by to check on us and grab extra silverware.

detailedReviews.author: Victoria Shepard
detailedReviews.text: There are a standard selection of brews as well as a rotating stock. Beers were awesome. I personally love the logo. However some of the sandwiches don't come with a side included which is sort of bizzare. Other than that, solid brewery

detailedReviews.author: Lisa T
detailedReviews.text:
Had my heart set on the chicken schnitzel sandwich after I saw a photo on their online ordering site. Went in person and is disappointed to see that it was just a fried chicken breast it wasn‚Äôt schnitzel at all. It wasn‚Äôt even pounded. I told the waiter and the waiter said well sometimes they can‚Äôt get it then they do the best they can and it‚Äôs hit or miss. They did not offer to remake it and I could not eat it. Too bad, Since I was really hopeful, I found a place that I could get schnitzel.
Pretzel soft and warm in the bear was cold though. We would not go back though.

detailedReviews.author: Larry Z
detailedReviews.text: Went for the first time and the bar tender was rude as they come. Asked about beers and she told me to look at the app.  After being ignored for 10 mi. She came back. I was talking to a waitress (super nice) I asked the bar tender what was a good flight. She responded I don‚Äôt know, I don‚Äôt know what you like. I left. Told her that she was rude from the moment I stepped in.  Also need better bar stools. Cheap medal ones.

detailedReviews.text: Service was great. Friendly, helpful staff. Had the Dog Park; the pepperoni stromboli was the best part. Space is a bit cramped.

Our server was Eric, and he was extremely knowledgeable, friendly, and an all around joy to spend the evening with‚Ä¶ he was helpful in helping us choose what we needed to drink, and his food recommendations were spot on.  Great atmosphere, standard prices, stellar service.  10/10! ‚ú®

detailedReviews.text: Such a great spot! Amazing food and drinks. We liked it so much we went here twice during our recent trip to the area!

detailedReviews.author: M Robinson
detailedReviews.text: Really enjoyed our visit to Wasserhund in late June while heading to OBX. Our server was awesome, the food was really very good, and their beer was pretty decent. I'll be back üëç

detailedReviews.author: Lisa Geiger
detailedReviews.text: Legit chicken sandwich. Good beers, and the pup approved.

detailedReviews.author: Angela Smith
detailedReviews.text: Just sat there for 10 minutes, completely ignored.  Even went to the bar and was ignored by three bartenders.  Never going there again.

detailedReviews.author: Justin Murrill
detailedReviews.text: In town for work and just happened to pass this place. Did a U-turn and was not disappointed. Delicious Lager and Brat with spicy mustard and sauerkraut. Excellent choice. Few German culinary choices and even fewer that are good. Wasserhund is king in HR!

detailedReviews.author: Alexandrea Sumuel Groves
detailedReviews.text: Our friends were in town with their pup, so we decided to give Wasserhund a try! The Hell Hound pizza was delicious and puppy loved his Pup Pie! Great service, too!

detailedReviews.author: nathan floyd
detailedReviews.text:
For over two years now, my girlfriend and I have been going to Wasserhund every Tuesday night for trivia. Eric has consistently been a friendly, accommodating, knowledgeable, and professional member of the Wasserhund team!
Eric takes great pride in making all patrons who walk in the door feel welcome! His knowledge of the food and drink menu is flawless, and his recommendations have never disappointed.
My girlfriend and I love going to trivia because of the host Jen, and we love going to trivia at Wasserhund because of Eric!

detailedReviews.author: Ron Doyle
detailedReviews.text: Very noisy, no sound absorption so sound excited and bands around. Beer was ok.

detailedReviews.author: Scott Agostinelli
detailedReviews.text: Nice place...

detailedReviews.author: Kellei Agostinelli
detailedReviews.text: Good beer, great food - best cauliflower crust I've ever had!

detailedReviews.author: Mike Farmer
detailedReviews.text: My wife and I go here at least twice a month. Amazing craft beer and fantastic food, especially üçï.

detailedReviews.author: Mark Pruim
detailedReviews.text: This was the closest brewery to out hotel... Thanks, Google. We had the "dog pile" and loaded tots (get your own Napoleon). I had a beer flight and my bride had a specialty drink. Outside seating area was a bit warm in the sun, thankfully there was a shaded area. Overall would definitely go back. Beer was upper end mid, if that makes sense (I've had better, but would come back)

detailedReviews.author: Kevin Amon
detailedReviews.text: Today, my wife and I came here for lunch. The food and atmosphere was great. The pizza was awesome. So much flavor and taste. I'm a pizzaholic. We both had a mango wheat beer. (Forgot the name) delicious.

detailedReviews.author: John Rice
detailedReviews.text: Cool vibe, great beer, and yummy food‚Ä¶staff were great too!

detailedReviews.author: Takiyah Brown
detailedReviews.text: Our first time at this Brewery and it did not disappoint! I tried a mimosa flight, fried pickles and the hot and honey chicken sandwich with some beer cheese fries. The food was great and the service was even better! We will return! Do not hesitate to drop in!

detailedReviews.author: Sam Jessurun
detailedReviews.text: Food was great, drinks were delicious, and the wait staff complimented me multiple times, so I'll definitely be going back.

detailedReviews.author: Chuck Farnsworth
detailedReviews.text: Neat place.  Stopped in because of the name and menu.  Food and service sold us on a return trip for the next time we are in the area.

detailedReviews.author: Ang Elion
detailedReviews.text: Great place to chill. The staff was awesome. Eric the manager is knowledgeable about what beers you may like.

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Riffle
detailedReviews.text: The brewery was fairly quiet this Sunday during my family‚Äôs visit. The brew I had was decent if not a bit overpriced. The food is fine but honestly nothing to write home about for the price. Overall, not too crazy but fairly reasonable experience.

detailedReviews.author: Milton Hill
detailedReviews.text: Enjoy the beer and food along with meeting new friends over trivia. Will return.

detailedReviews.author: Matt Henry
detailedReviews.text: This place is fine. Beers are fine, service is fine, location is fine. Just not overly impressed with anything‚Ä¶

detailedReviews.author: Mike Arrigo
detailedReviews.text: Beer was ok.  Food was great.

detailedReviews.author: Fadi Kalouch
detailedReviews.text: Elizabeth was AMAZING!!! I will be back every week just because of her!!!

detailedReviews.author: Shaun Johnson
detailedReviews.text: Very enjoyable. Staff is friendly, welcoming, and accommodating. Highly recommend the pizza!

detailedReviews.author: Chad Morrison
detailedReviews.text:
Awesome place.
Great service.
Atmosphere is fun and inviting.

Highly recommend to locals and travelers!

Great job wasserhund!
